 shaped Spenser’s literary milieu will be indispensable to teachers of the Renaissance period, to students of comic literature, and to established Spenserians.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aShakespeare 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aHumour.  aProtestantism.  aRenaissance literature.  aallegory.  abathos.  aclassical literature.  acomic theory.  aepic.  amedieval literature.  asatire.1 a Coldham-Fussell, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613112640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526131126423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526131126/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles